reviews: Location is decent and staff are friendly. We stayed in a triple room, the size was OK but it was very dark and there was a weird, unpleasant smell in the room throughout the stay. The ‘courtyard’ for the triple rooms is kept untidy and is not private. The rooms could do with a refresh.

We would definitely stay at hotel des nations st-German again staff were very friendly and helpful suggesting areas to visit and lovely restaurants to eat at. Good location we walked a lot from here and felt area was very safe.

Check in was quick an helpful reception staff . Never same staff on desk all 4 nites we stayed . Room was small as expected but the carpets and curtains were dirty .fridge didn’t work was just hot an smelly so we unplugged it . Sleep quality was poor due to noisy guests an being side of lift . The breakfast wS ok but no Decaff coffee and no breakfast tea either . The breakfast room an reception appeared to have a upgrade but this didn’t apply anywhere else . Overall the location was good plenty of restaurants and bars walkable an two metro stops very close . Wouldn’t book again .

Curtains of the room dusty as well as the floor .
The menu of the room was dirty of food .
Phone in the room wasn’t working .
Ac filters have not been cleaned .
We asked some information to the staff but they didn’t help us that much .

Liked · good location and good wifi

Disliked · Tiny room 250 cm by 350 cm, bed only 180 cm long and 145 cm wide, shower only 60 cm by 60 cm, cracks in wash basin and toilet hood. space for wash basin too tight to spread your arms. not possible to fill the watercooker under the tap. a drinking glass had to be used. No printed or video channel guide in the room with telephone numbers to call in emergency and nowhere a mentioning of the telephone number of the reception desk. We one evening ran out of toilet paper because the cleaning lady had forgotten and had to go down to the reception desk ourselves. Outside of the building looked neglected While checking out the reception did not enquire after our satisfaction with the stqy.

We did not enjoy our stay in this hotel. The quality of the room was extremely poor and unclean. The carpet, bed throws and pillows all had stains on them.
The room itself was very small. As we had baggage, it left us feeling extremely cramped. We asked for an upgrade for a larger room, which we would pay for, and the concierge was not very accommodating and declined.
The air conditioning didn’t work, so the room was very hot which was not comfortable in any way.
The concierge upon departure was lovely however, and greeted us with a smile. This was the only positive to our stay.
Very unhappy with the overall stay and cleanliness of the room.

Although the staff was friendly, my overall experience was unpleasant. The room (#55) was small, and the bathroom was tiny and unclean with moisture on the walls! The worst part was the overpowering smell of moisture or sewage in both the bedroom and bathroom, forcing me to keep the windows open when the temperature was as low as 3°C - and getting no sleep at all.

I do not recommend booking a taxi through the hotel as the driver will charge you an extra 7€ without prior notice from the hotel.

Stayed for one night after Eurostar issues. Location is at the heart of the Left Bank and the staff were very friendly and helpful.

Room was clean and completely as described. A great base for exploring Paris.

Great location (near Cardinal Lemoine metro station) and perfect for us as a family of 4 (10 and 14 years). Compact rooms but very comfortable beds and ideal hotel for a 3 night stay. Friendly and helpful staff who are bilingual and can answer any questions. Great breakfast selection and plenty of it. 10-15 minute to get to the hop on/hop off bus tour. 4 minute walk to get to a choice of restaurants on Rue Moufftard (sp?). We would stay here again.

Perfect service, perfect location, small rooms en very small bathroom, but you know that when you go to Paris. Don't book breakfast, that was scanty and not varying. For example, there were no boiled eggs/

Stayed in a very charming room at the 6th floor with balconies towards the street with a view over the roofs. Along the street were small lokal shops with frukt and vegetables, butchers,boulangerie, patisserie and restaurants.

This hotel was the worse part of our wonderful trip to Paris. The receptionist who checked us in was rude. There was a male sitting in the reception area and they apparently had " issues." Our room was so small that we could not even walk around the bed once we brought in our carry on luggage. We were given another larger room which was better. However, the carpeting in the hallway and our room was stained and gross, there were pubic hairs in the bathroom and on the window that opened out onto the street! It smelled , we spent our first night ( booked thru travel agent for 5 nights) looking for a new hotel. I cleaned the bathroom and we slept with windows open. We ended up staying as the location was the best! We could walk everywhere. Breakfast was ok, nothing great. The dining area was very clean and the ladies kept the food filled. They were also very nice. The rest of the staff except for the aforementioned rude person were great. Nicole was very helpful to us. Despite it being on a very busy street, we slept well.

Lovely staff, clean rooms, ideal location. Would recommend to stay here again. Easy walk to notre damn from the hotel. Multiple metro stations nearby too. Easy access to Disneyland about 1 hour door to door on the train

A minute or so to two different subway lines, this hotel is in an excellent location for those wanting an authentic Parisian feel. It's close to the Parthenon, Sorbonne and dozens of restaurants, plus it's just across the street from some Roman arena ruins, which makes for a nice, contemplative green-space. The rooms are fairly small, but typical for the Haussmann design. The carpeting is a little worse for wear and the modern shine is starting to fade a bit; probably in need of refurb in the next couple of years, but for now, it's part of the charm. Street noise was not a problem with my back-facing room but the hallway conversations could easily be heard through the closed door. Fortunately, the other guests were quiet and respectful. The staff were helpful, professional and efficient, The breakfast was delicious, just make sure it's included or not as that wasn't entirely clear upon check-in.

We were so happy with our small but perfectly formed room, the facilities were perfect. The receptionist area was efficient warm and friendly, as were all the staff. Nothing was too much trouble, and even with our pigeon French they were wonderful to deal and communicate with. I’m so sorry I didn’t get everyone’s names as all the staff were wonderful and to top it off our last morning’s breakfast was comped by the lovely receptionist, it ended our visit on a high and are already recommending this hotel thank you for a wonderful stay in your beautiful city 🇫🇷

Upon arriving, Melania - Hotel representative was very courteous in checking us in. The breakfast included scrambled eggs, bacon, chocolate croissant, cold cereal, juice, coffee and tea. The room was small as was the shower(4'x 4'). Basic accomodations would not fit anybody too large. For me and my wife - small stature, it was fine.

Very good hotel in a wonderful area of Paris. Rooms are small (which is pointed out perfectly in the description), but very clean and you even have a small minibar. We were given a room on the 2nd floor with no view at all, but when I complained about that at the reception desk they immediately gave us a room on the 5th floor with street view. It even had a very small balcony from which you could see the Notre Dame and the Sacre Coeur!! The breakfast is very good but you have to be early to get something warm like eggs, bacon etc. These items did not get a refill, which is the only negative thing I can say. Lovely cappuccino!

Wonderful location, very close to two Metro stations. Easy walk to some of the main attractions along the Seine and many restaurant and bar options.
Rooms were neat and comfortable (not large - but that is expected in Paris!).
Staff on reception were very helpful and friendly!

Great hotel, room perfect size for the busy guest who wants a quiet sleep, airy room and hot shower. And a lift. Metro across.the street and another 100m meters away. Plenty of choice of places to eat , small supermarkets.and grocery stores nearby. In 20 minutes on metro we could arrive at any part of the city and there was.plenty within walking distance, not.least the Sorbonne and Notre Dame and the Pantheon, St Germain, Cafe de Flore.

I very much liked the reception who seem very concerned about doing their job well with clients. They take care of all details to make sure everything was done correctly. In my case I had to find some structure I wasn’t even sure about the name and passed some time with receptionist to find what exactly I was looking for and she helped a lot!

I was quite happy with my stay. The room was modern and clean, with good wifi and AC (it wasn't huge, but that can't be expected in Paris). It was in a good location for my trip, and I was particularly pleased with the breakfast.

We would not stay at this hotel again because the service is terrible. The front desk does not respond to emails regarding existing bookings. When you reserve a taxi, the front desk does not inform you about booking and luggage fees. The carpets in our room were stained and old. We found a large spider on our bed. Fortunately, we spotted the insect so it wouldn’t crawl on us when we were sleeping. Hotel Monge across the street looks much better (we will stay there next time). Hotel Fabric is also a great choice in Le Marais. Hotel positives are 1) good location, 2) two Metro stops nearby and 3) breakfast lady was friendly and helpful (she should be in charge of the hotel).

I stayed here for 3 nights with my sister on a short break to Paris. The hotel is in a quiet but safe area of Paris and we were happy to walk around the area in the evening and found a few nice places to eat nearby. There is also a supermarket very close. The rooms were small but were adequate for our needs as we were out most of the day and they were clean and comfortable. There are two metro stations very close by as well as being a 15-20 minute walk from the Notre dame. For us, the hotel was in a manageable location to visit the city but it is a little out so the good public transport links help. I would return as it was well located but quiet so we could get a good night's sleep.

Having read a few reviews about the size of everything I was apprehensive before our visit. However! This hotel is amazing from start to finish. Are the rooms a little small-perhaps but if you’re there to see Paris and not spend your day in the hotel room then you’re in the right place. The staff were friendly. Every single one of them. The hotel was clean and our room had a lovely balcony and view. The street although a main road is quiet and we slept with the door ajar. It’s across the road from metro, walking distance to tourist attractions and amazing restaurants. We will definitely be returning and recommending to our friends and family. So glad we found this gem on our first visit to Paris.

Rooms very small and shower almost unfit for purpose . Hotel clean and tidy BEWARE . If hotel call a taxi for you 7 EURO SURCHARGE and fare verges on extortion . Not informed by hotel of this fact and short trip to Luxembourg station doubled in price as a result . Good price food available nearby and it’s handy for getting around .

We stayed for 6 nights during a recent trip to France. The reception staff was very welcoming. The hotel is in a great location close to both the Cardinal Lemoine and Monge stations. So very easy to get around Paris. There are great restaurants within walking distance to the hotel. The hotel and our room was spotlessly clean. While not overly large, compared to the rooms of friends who were also staying at the hotel, it was decent size with a large bathroom. Two things keep this from being a 5 star review - the noise that carried over from other rooms on our floor. It seemed that the walls were paper thin. The other thing is that the mattress was super firm which is frequently the case in Europe, but still after 6 nights, we were ready for a change. It would have been nice to have a chair in the room rather than the 2 upholstered ottomans. Given the bed was not comfortable to begin with, having it as the only sitting option wasn’t too wonderful. As we booked on the hotel website, we did have breakfast included. It was fine and not dissimilar to other continental breakfasts offered by other hotels.

This hotel is perfect for a short stay.
It’s in a good position.
Personnel is really kind and it’s clean.
Rooms are tidy and not too small.
I would definitely return.
Metro is really close and there is a supermarket few minutes walking.
There are a lot of restaurants nearby and take away shops.
It’s not in the center of Paris, but it’s close to the Sorbonne University
Francesca

This popular saying in business exemplifies how this *outstanding* gem of a hotel cares for people. On a trip to Paris alone, during the January 202 strikes, I got lost as my phone battery died. I stopped in this hotel to inquire on directions.

The front desk team didn't just assist with directions. They charged my phone, called me a taxi, and offered me tea while I waited, inviting me to rest in their beautiful lounge. Mind you, I was not a guest of this hotel. Any hotel whose staff takes care of a random visitor as these people took care of me that winter evening is providing top-tier 5-star service to their paying guests. This quiet hotel conveniently nestled in the heart of Paris, is a jewel.

This hotel is in a great location and really good value for money for Paris. The actual bedroom was quite small, but had everything you would need and was well laid out. It had a balcony with a view to the Sacre Coeur. There are some rooms that are bigger, so may be worth asking when booking. It didn't trouble us as we spent very little time in the hotel as there was so much to see and do. All the staff were polite and friendly - would stay again.

We have just returned from our trip to Paris and stayed at this hotel. The hotel was in a great location near many bars and shops and less than 3 minutes from the Metro. All staff were helpful and polite and the room was very clean and modern. My boyfriend had very kindly asked for chocolates on our arrival and they were sitting ready - a lovely touch! The 2 things I would highlight as creating the 4/5 stars would be the very small bathroom which was difficult to navigate and the fact you could hear lots of noises from other guests in various parts of the hotel. Overall, we thoroughly enjoyed staying at the hotel as it suited the style of our trip and would 100% recommend to people wanting a good priced and accessible hotel in Paris.

We stayed for 2 nights at the hotel. The room was spotless and nicely decorated, if a touch on the small side. The bathroom was also spotless and the only negative is that the shower was affixed to the side wall over the bath rather than at the end wall!

The reception team were all very friendly and welcoming, gave great suggestions on where to head for nearby bars/restaurants (rue moffetard, which runs parallel to the street this hotel is on)

The location was great, midway between two metro stops, 15mins walk to Notre Dame, as mentioned Rue Moffetard was within a few minutes walk and had plenty of bars/restaurants to choose from, it had a busy vibe and was obviously popular with Sorbonne students - I can highly recommend eating at La Fontaine de la Mouffe- they do a 3 course menu offer starting from €19 with very generous portion sizes!

Overall I would recommend this hotel and would stay here again!

Decided to stay here with my husband for our 6 nights in Paris, as I stayed here with my two daughters three years ago. Booked direct with the hotel, as the rate was better then I had seen posted, and booking direct got us free breakfast at the hotel. So the hotel itself is in a great location, in between two metro stops, so easy to get around. Also just around the corner from the Latin Quarter, so just up a few stairs and you are in a nice quiet area filled with lots of restaurants, and shops. The room at the hotel was exactly as I had expected, on the smaller size, however it was fine for the two of us, as I asked for a room with two twins as the math added to a bigger bed then the one double in the other rooms. This time our room faced the back of the hotel, so very very quiet. Breakfast was ok, lots of coffee, baguette, croissants, and yogurt. The scrambled eggs looked strange as everything is microwaved in the small kitchenette attached to the breakfast room, happy to have used this as it did save us some funds, as Paris is pretty expensive. Overall I would stay here again, as it is really convenient to so many sights, Notre Dame is just down the street a bit.

Thanks for a great stay Hotel Des Nations. I stayed with my Mum for a three night break. All these other people complaining about the size, this is Paris. Respect the difference ! We loved it such a fab area full of character and charm. The hotel staff were all lovely and helpful, for the price too in the capital city of France was superb. Would not come close to this standard in London. Thanks again x

The hotel is in a desperate need of an upgrade. The carpets are badly stained in the rooms and in the hallways. Walls are scuffed and marked in the rooms and on the rest of the hotel floor. The bathroom is ridiculously tiny and the shower almost unusable because of the small space. Think the size of a cruise ship bathroom but even smaller. The shower curtain was stained and the toliet was cracked. To top it off there was a horrible mildew smell in the room and the AC unit did not work, which required us to sleep with the windows open which thankfully it was a cool time of year. For the price and the location I would definitely look somewhere else before booking. We had stayed at another hotel at the beginning of our trip in Paris that was cheaper, bigger, cleaner and in a way better location. Would not recommend staying at this hotel unless they did some serious renovations.

I stayed for ten days with my parents and it was fantastic! My dad is on a wheelchair and cannot walk and he could access all areas in our room. The bathroom was great for him! Very wheelchair friendly hotel and located in a nice area. Notre Dame is somewhat close to it and we had no issues getting Uber to and from the location of the hotel. There was a Carrefour (supermarket) nearby that had everything we needed.

Aside from the smallest shower I have ever seen, this hotel was a pleasant surprise. Clean, comfortable and ideally located between two beautiful parks - Luxembourg and Jardin des Plants. Great service, modern updated rooms and comfortable beds. I would stay again.

I enjoyed my stay at the Hotel des Nations. It is very comfortable. The breakfast room and breakfast are excellent. It is in a nice location, right near two subway lines, a short walk to the Seine, le Jardin des Plantes, the Natural History Museum and place de la Contrascarpe. The hotel staff is excellent.

Location is superb and hotel is spotlessly clean. Check-in and check-out were ok but leaving luggage seemed a big ask! Would definitely stay again - the views from the top floor balcony were amazing. Rooms are quite small but well stocked and very comfortable. Didn’t take breakfast as seemed quite expensive and lots of cafes nearby.

Great location with friendly staffs, no stereotype at the hotel, small but comfortable room. Simple , clean and functional hotel. Great value for money. Very helpful and friendly front house.
I will definitely stay again and recommend to others!!!

I think I have a new favorite hotel in Paris. It's just 2-3 blocks away from metro station that easily connects to CDG airport and a 10 min walk from Notre Dame and the Seine. Lot's of places to eat nearby. Staff is very nice and helpful. Wifi is good. Tiny bathroom and room in general, but everything looks new and is comfortable. Anyway, if you're in Paris you hardly spend time in the room! For me the best time was value for money, it's a great hotel with a nice street view, close to everything and at a very affordable price.

We spent 5 nights here, it really became our home while in Paris! Good use of space with lots of shelving for devices, food, etc. We were lucky enough to have one of only two rooms with a shared/private courtyard. I made a mistake and booked for 6 nights instead of 5 and they only charged me for the 5 nights. Breakfast was definitely satisfactory but I’m not a big breakfast eater. Carrefour grocery store 2 minutes walk and Tons of restaurant options.

This hotel is simple and clean. The location on Rue Monge is excellent; easy to get to the Rue Mouffetard area or catch the Metro 7 line to other parts of Paris. There are some cafes along the Rue Monge including further south toward Place Monge that are fun. The price/value is very good compared to other Paris hotels. It's not fancy, and the lobby is plain, but the rooms are clean and the bathrooms reasonably updated. The staff is competent, albeit, a little French helps.

An excellent hotel in a great location in the heart of Paris. Very good breakfast with many choices. Very good and friendly service. I highly recommend it and I would definitely choose it again for a stay in Paris.

We were greeted in Paris by very friendly and helpful staff at Hotel des Nations St-Germain. Our room was pleasantly decorated, well stocked and had a great view! Our only disappointment was that when we entered the room there was a very very large and fresh looking stain on the carpet. It was blood red and about a foot wide. It looked as though they had tried to put bleach on it to clean it as there was a discoloured white/yellowy spot in the middle. It was just off putting. We checked in quite late and left in the morning so I did not fuss with getting another room. I would give the Hotel des Nations St-Germain a second try though!

Nice clean rooms, not big - but we had everything we needed. We didn’t eat breakfast there because there are so many options in the neighborhood (which is really lovely). Perfect location, quiet but really close to everything and just across the road from metro.

My daughter and i spent now three nights at Hotel Agora Saint Germain. We enjoyed the hotel very much. It is a small hotel, in a very good location in the latin quarter, very close to a number of subway stations. The rooms are small but comfortable with a mini bar and a kettle. The staff is very friendly and helpful, and gave us very good recommendations.tge area is great, close to many attractions. We would love tocome back.
Ariela Mann
Israel

Stayed here for 5 nights. Room was really small, but that’s usually the case in Paris. Our room was located in the first floor next to the elevator and it felt like living under a bowling alley with all that noice. It was mentioned that we would have air conditioning and street view, but we didn’t have either. The room got really hot during the night so we had trouble sleeping. Minibar was plugged in and on, but it was only room temperature. The small shower had almost no water pressure and it was also dirty. For a three star hotel in quartier latin it was okay I guess, but I think that for a rate of 150 € a night you can find better deals. ‬

Pros:
The staff is very helpful! They were welcoming, kind, and answered many questions. The breakfast is definitely worth it! There were many choices for dietary restrictions and it was fresh, tasty, and cleanly laid out. The hotel is in a good location. It’s very near to the metro stations but it’s also easy to walk to sites like Notre Dame, which was about a 15/20 minute walk. The area was quiet and close to many restaurants and shops.

Cons:
The room was small and cozy, but not the cleanest. The carpets, curtains and bedding were stained. The bed had a big dip in the center and was hard, which made it uncomfortable. There is no cold air conditioning and the water was sometimes cold. There was no restock of toiletries, but the front desk happily gave us more. Our room was not stocked with enough towels and no washcloths. Lastly, and most importantly, the wifi sucked!

Hotel is situated in a very convenient area, close to two metro stations but only 10-15mins walk from central areas, so very good. Rooms while small are not as cramped as many Paris hotels, staff friendly, breakfast buffet breakfast very good.

There's a lot to love about Hotel Des Nations. It's conviently located near the Metro 7. The Rue Mouffetard is right behind it. The front desk staff are almost surprisingly helpful and accommodating (this is Paris). The rooms are adequate. We stayed on the 6th floor. The bathroom was very clean -the towel warmer was a nice addition to The carpet was, well, ewwwww. It was filthy and stained. This was the only detriment. The breakfast was lovely. Good coffee and nice pastry can cover a multitude of sins.

We preferred a less touristy area and that's what we got-lots of local Parisians, university students, restaurants, boulangeries, flower shops, cafes but still close to all of the tourist spots via metro or on foot. The hotel room for 4 was expectedly small with 2 double beds put together and 2 single pull-out couches, tastefully decorated, had windows opening to the inner courtyard, serene though a little dated (stained carpet and rickety table). Again space is very tight especially with the couches pulled out but it was manageable and we really didn't stay much in the room. The shower, like most European showers, was awkward since it only had a 2 foot glass enclosure that didn't prevent water from spilling onto the floor and there wasn't much space to put your toiletries. Nevertheless, the staff was friendly and helpful and the ambience was casual and comfortable. We opted not to purchase the $16 per person breakfast since it was much cheaper to buy baked goods from the aromatic boulangeries nearby. If you want to eat and shop your way through Paris, this is the place to go. Overall, we had an enjoyable experience at the Hotel des Nations St. Germain.

We stayed for 3 nights and it is very cozy and in a good locations.
There are many places to go around and we enjoyed the time. Actually the location allows you not to use public transport if you are traveling for leisure - Notre Dame is about 15 minutes by foot, Luxemburg garden - the same. 30 minutes of walk and you are in Mare. Everything is close to this place!

The location is great and this is what justify the money you pay to stay there. It is only 12-15 mins walk to Notre Dame. The street is full of shops and lovely coffee places and restaurants can be found juts around the corner. Uber can be ordered within couple of minutes as it is a very central and well connected location. The rooms however are tiny! We were expecting it to be small, however two people are not able to walk through the room. One person had to be sat on a bed so the other could go through to the bathroom. There is no space for two suitcases to be placed anywhere without actually obstructing the access to the bathroom, the content of the suitcase cannot be unpacked easily. The bathroom was as big as a room which is so unnecessary. Another obstacle for me was very low pressure in the shower (with regards to washing hair and removing the shampoo properly- mission impossible). Only one tiny shower gel has been provided- not enough for two adults. Otherwise clean and the staff at the reception very welcoming.

Hotel des Nations St. Germain is superbly located between two metro stations, making it an excellent home base for a Paris adventure. It’s also located near the Latin Quarter and street markets, so you’ll never run out of sumptuous food choices, from bakeries to small crepe shops and bistros. There is a convenience store and laundromat nearby, essential for any traveller.The rooms were quite small though, and it was a struggle to fit two medium sized suitcases. Though there was a built in closet to hang clothes, flat surfaces were at premium so storage was a challenge. The room was well lit, opening up to a small balcony which stood over Rue de Monge, making for a pleasant vantage point for watching people go about their business on the street below. The hotel is on a busy avenue, but it is a nice neighbourhood and quiet in the evenings. Wifi is strong and fast, allowing us to stream movies which was good as the TV only had local channels. The bed was nice and comfortable, eager to receive our tired bodies after a days worth of Parisian jaunts. Speaking of tired, while the bathrooms were clean and fully functional, it seemed in need of a bed of its own to refresh itself. The in-room amenities were sparse, other hotels in this price range would usually have slippers, a wide assortment of toiletries, and coffee making facilities other than a kettle and some packets of desiccated coffee beans. While we did ask the front desk for some slippers and a much needed sewing kit, unfortunately they had run out of those luxuries.Based on the fire-escape floor plan, our room was already one of the larger ones - which to me would mean that the other rooms would best fit single occupants or vertical sleepers. Our room door was also at a disadvantageous position, being directly opposite the lift - which made us privy to the plans for the day of other occupants, which they discussed with fervour while waiting for the single lift to make its way up to the narrow hallways.Most of the staff were very friendly and welcoming, and the breakfast gave us enough fuel for our daily trek. It had all the essentials - fruit, juice, coffee, wonderful pastries, delectable cold cuts and cheeses, and of course the requisite eggs, bacon and sausages.Overall a solid hotel in an excellent location, so we would still definitely consider this hotel again for our next visit to Paris.

Good location with restaurants nearby. Close to the metro station. The room was very small which we knew before booking. However there was basically no space for two suitcases to be opened, and one had to be on the floor barring easy access to the bathroom. Difficult to figure out how to use the shower instead of drawing water for a bath. Only one tiny soap to serve both hand washing and shower. What really was disappointing was the fact I pointed out to reception there were cobwebs all around the ceiling. She wrote it down, presumably to have the maid clean. It never happened on our 3 night stay. Helpful at reception for verifying and printing boarding passes and also the car to pick us up for transport to the airport early in the morning. Do not think I would book this hotel again.

The hotel is close to 2 metro stations and walking distance to quite a few landmarks. I think it has been recently refurbished and is clean and modern. The breakfast is good and staff are very helpful. Good value for the price.

This is an excellent hotel for what you are paying for. Rooms are modern and clean, although somewhat small, but this is Paris and small is what you are going to get.

Breakfast consists of cereals, pastries and fruit and it sufficient to keep you going until lunch time.

The biggest plus is the location. There is a Carrefour close to hotel where supplies for the day can be purchased. There is an entrance to Place Monge metro station in Rue Des Arenes, 1 minute away from hotel. Turn right as you exit hotel, cross the road at pedestrian crossing and turn left at first road. I discovered this entrance on 2nd last day. Notre Dame and River Seine is a short walk from hotel. St Michel RAR station is in walking distance, this station takes you to Versailles Palace. The restaurants in Rue Mouffetard and shopping in Rue St Jacques is close by. Jardin des Plantes is around the corner.

First time to Paris and we were so happy with our hotel chocie. Traveled with our teenager and room accommodations fit our needs (1 full bed and 1 pullout chair). We were cozy and had everything we needed. Very clean & modern. Breakfast had more than enough options. Location close to many restaurants and Metro stops. The hotel pictures featured on this page are exactly what we experienced. We'd stay here again!

Nice modern little hotel in a great location, near shops and bars etc and 20 min walk from Notre damn. Only downfalls were: coffee was not replaced after first day, the bathroom was very small so every time you got out the shower you were basically sat on the toilet, and the shower kept turning as we were using it and sometimes sprayed water all over the floor. Other that than, a nice little hotel, clean, good value for money and good location.

This hotel was perfect for our stay. It is located about a 20 - 25 minute walk from Notre Dame.

Lots of local places to pick up baked goods and groceries. Also there is a metro stop a couple of blocks away which also had a local market on one of the days where we picked up some great cheese and meat.

The hotel itself - the room was small as was the elevator (also normal). The wifi didn't really work well, I noticed a sign in the elevator to rent a portable wifi device for your trip which I did on our last day - it too didn't really work so it was a waste of money to rent. I mentioned it to the staff and they just shrugged their shoulders with no comment.

I would say this is a good, well priced hotel with no frills.

I would consider staying again if other options were more expensive.

"Travelled as a family of 4 and stayed in the quadruple room. It was certainly on the cozy side but we knew that prior to arriving. Our large suitcases made it a little tricky but this is in no way a reflection on the hotel- rather our inability to travel light!
Breakfast was adequate and included in our booking. The location is perfect and within long leisurely walks to famous landmarks and very close to public transport. There are fantastic restaurants in the nearby vicinity. Staff were very welcoming and friendly. Would certainly stay here again!

I stayed at the Hotel des Nations St-Germain for 4 nights. The hotel is ideally located in the Latin Quarter and offers good value for money. The hotel is also close to Metro stations and has good amenities near by. The hotel staff are friendly and professional.

Great location close to many restaurants and points of interest! Clean and comfortable rooms, helpful staff that are willing to help as much as they can! I highly recommend adding a bottle of champagne and macaroons to your reservation! It’s worth the price to have them ready in the room, a perfect way to start a trip in Paris!

This is a very good hotel that is well located in the Latin Quarter. It is within a block of 2-different Metro stations. We had a very nice room. Well appointed, A/C, roomy bath, very clean, and very friendly & helpful staff. Easy walking distance to Place de la Contrescarpe. A delightful place to hangout evenings. Walk past Blvd. St. Germaine on way to Norte Dame (10-minutes).

Great choice . ill do it again and again..Welcoming staff. Very clean rooms.Shower was great even though others said it too small but its not.Location is great.I just think they need to add some more option on breakfast like vegetables and more cheese ..but other than that really great hotel that I would recommend.

This was the second stay for someone from the family with this hotel. It did't disappoint. The area is very safe. Close to two Metro lines. The rooms are small but very comfortable and clean. I liked their breakfast. Good variety, very fresh. Staff super friendly, helpful, and knowledgeable. They really make customers feel home, resolve all problems, give good suggestions. Many thanks to the staff!

We stayed here three nights. Check in was fine. All the staff were very good at this hotel except for one gentleman who just walked away from us after we asked for help one evening. I wish I had gotten his name... However, the most disappointing thing to me was how dirty the rooms were. The rooms were small and the shower extremely small but whatever; that’s not necessarily important to me. However, when the shower curtain is so mildewed and stinky that you feel grossed out touching it, it’s a problem. Honestly, how much does it cost to replace a small plastic shower curtain? The room itself smelled musty and sour. The carpets had obviously not been vacuumed and were very stained. There was hair on the floor in the bathroom. I notified the front desk and they did come and vacuum at least but the carpets badly need to be replaced. They are filthy! I am assuming by other reviews that some rooms must be better because I booked on the basis of good reviews and was so disappointed... On a positive note, the location was great, the breakfast was good. As noted above, most staff were great and eager to assist. I would never stay here again - very disappointed...

Small is definitely the best way to describe the room we stayed in a few weeks ago. More on that below...

First of all, let's start with the positives. The first positive is the location. The Latin quarter is a good base to experience Paris. There's a lively strip of restaurants and bars about 5 minutes away, which we had some great meals and nights out. Only a few doors down on the same street is the best restaurant we had the pleasure of dining at in our month long trip called Hugo & Co. This is a must visit. Also, the very underrated Pantheon is only about a 5 minute walk away. In regards to the other landmarks, Notre Dame Cathedral (about 15 minutes), Louvre (40 minutes) and the Eiffel Tower (a bit over an hour) are all walk-able.

The next positive was the service of the man when we checked in. He was friendly and very helpful when pointing out the main sights of the area. He gave us a lot of good tips and was very knowledgeable.

Now to the negatives. The first one is definitely in regards to the size of the room. The room was extremely small. There wasn't a lot of room to move. The bathroom as well was tiny. The shower would have to be the smallest we have every seen. So small in fact that you are either touching and sticking to the shower curtain or the taps. We would hate to think how people would manage if they were on the larger side.

In addition to this, we were a bit disappointed with the cleanliness of the room. When we first arrived we noticed dried up leaves sitting on top of the bed under a pillow and a piece of chewed up gum lying on the floor. This really was off putting to see straight away and didn't get us off onto a good note.

Lastly, the noise in the room was really bad. I had to use earplugs because we were right next to the lift, which was so noisy and clunky. This seemed to run and shake the room almost all night. Also, the rooms on our level were very noisy, meaning they were extremely loud talkers or the walls were paper thin.

All in all, our stay was jut okay. We might have got a bad few days, so apologies if this was the case. The hotel has a bit to offer in terms of location, it was just a bit disappointing in some other aspects.

This hotel is in a real Paris neighborhood, not a touristy area. We did a bit of exploring, and no matter which direction you go, there are a lot of cafes, shops and restaurants to choose from. On Sunday, half a block from the hotel, was an open air market with meats, cheeses, fish, fruits, vegetables, flowers and more. It was crowded with people from the neighborhood doing all their shopping. I walked to the Notre Dame area every day (a 10 minute walk) where there are a lot of outdoor vendors, several bus stops, the hop-on-hop-off bus, walking along the river. I even walked to the Louvre. The hotel itself is nice, the staff is great, and the bed is so comfortable, I did not want to get up. BUT, my bathroom could have been a bit cleaner. The tub really needed a good scrubbing. If you're a light sleeper, bring earplugs. The hallways are noisy, and I could hear the woman in the next room sneezing! Also, I don't know what the smoking policy at the hotel is, but the hallways were smoky at night. I would stay here again.

A good hotel in a convenient location and a pleasant neighbourhood - 5 minutes walk from the metro station Cardinal Lemoine. We had a nice street view from a little balcony. Functional, clean room which had all the basic amenities plus an efficient and cheerful housekeeping lady.
The room was definitely tiny( not sure what the rooms in other hotels in Paris are like), and so was the bathtub.
Was there was five nights and wasn’t too pleased with the breakfast experience after the first day there- while the breakfast wasn’t bad in itself, the experience was below average. The lady in the breakfast room never looked happy about doing her job.
The receptionists and housekeeping staff were accommodating and friendly.

My colleague and I had to stay here no choice so we did try our best to make the most of it..

Positives - friendly staff and 10 mins walk from the river.

Negatives - the wifi did not work AT ALL during our week long stay. Not in our rooms or in the lobby. Quite a few people were complaining about this. This was a big issue as we had to log in for work in the evenings so actually had to go to other hotels and use their wifi instead which was not practical at all.
- Paris rooms are small so that’s fine but the only place to put clothes was a dirty rail over the fridge which was too small for coats and longer garments. And just a few broken hangers. No drawers or shelves or anything else.
- The fridge in my room does not work. The light comes on but the fridge isn’t cold at all and is actually warm and I had to throw a load of my food away. The inside of the fridge (and my colleague’s fridge) were absolutely caked in thick yellow and brown leaked liquid and food. It was disgusting (have uploaded photos).
- The carpet in my room was stained and hadn’t been hoovered (photos uploaded). As we checked in late housekeeping wasn’t able to clean for me and the hotel was fully booked so couldn’t switch rooms. The cleaner in fact did not clean the room once during our stay, she just made the beds. The dirty sticky table surface was never cleaned and I had to do this myself.
- The shower in my room was too small to fit an adult in and I had to shower half over the sink which flooded the bathroom every-time. The ceiling in the bathroom was yellow and had a leak- assume this was from the guest above having the same flooding issues as me. Pieces of the ceiling were falling down everyday (photos attached). The free shower gel bottles were open and had been used. All of the towels on the first day had gross brown stains on and I had to ask for replacements. The once white shower curtain was pink and yellow with staining and covered in mould. The sink was cracked and chipped.
- The air con in my room didn’t work at all and it was boiling outside. Slept the first night with the windows open but awoke to find the entire room filled with smoke. The couple next door were smoking out of their window and worryingly the smoke alarms weren’t going off. I complained to reception and was told that smoking was prohibited. Yes I said, that was the issue! They didn’t do anything about it so every morning between 5-6am I was woken up by the thick smoke in my room that made me really sick.
- The elevator shakes the whole building when it stops on a floor and the walls are not sound proof at all so god help you if you have kids in the rooms next door like my colleague.
- Rooms do not come with irons. My colleague asked for one on the first day and never got one. We heard the receptionist knocking on other guests doors asking if they were done using the 3 whole irons that the hotel had, but we were told that they were all in use for the whole week. As we were travelling on business this was very annoying as shirts couldn’t be ironed!
- Breakfast. What a poor affair. The chairs were all stained. The variety is small: sausages on sticks, bacon, cups of runny scrambled eggs, fruit from a can, bread, two kinds of cereal and some mini pastries. That’s it. But worst of all this is not replenished throughout the morning so it’s first come first served even if you’ve paid extra for the breakfast. There were a lot of Americans staying so one day at 8am all of the bread and pastries had already gone and the lady serving didn’t seem to care. Nutella packets are also rationed by her. She told me off for having 2 packets because its only one per guest each morning!

During our stay guests were always at reception complaining about the food, rooms and wifi. All of the Americans said they had moved rooms about 6 times. 2 Chinese girls checked out early and went to another hotel. Another couple checked out after one night and went to another hotel. Given how many things were wrong with this place I cannot understand where all of the bad reviews are??!?!!! Are these reviews even real? Would not recommend this place to anyone.

Small rooms, but cosy, great location and staff were very friendly and accommodating with excellent English. Would definitely stay here again on a return visit as the location was fantastic and overall, great value for money.

Myself and my partner stayed here for 7 days in August. Because of the price and location we weren't expecting anything amazing but we're really impressed with what we got. Bedroom is reasonably sized and even had a balcony in which you could see Notre dame and sacre cour. Bathroom was small, especially the shower but we expected this. The staff were lovely and helpful and the location is perfect, great for transport toother parts of the city.

Friendly and helpful staff, rooms are clean, comfortable and quiet. Great location between Metro 10 and 7 (basically all you need to get around Paris, also walking distance to Notre-Dame. Highly recommend.

Our room was on the ground floor in a little courtyard. It was nicely decorated, but a little idiosyncratic. The bathroom had a wet floor for the shower. It was nearly impossible to keep the water contained, though we tried.

The greeting by reception staff was a little cold. Not unfriendly, but not exactly welcoming either. Our room, off a courtyard behind reception, was near a door to a basement, where some of the staff seemed to hang out. There seemed to be quite a lot of heated discussion, bordering on argument, but as I don't speak French I can't say for sure.

The biggest oversight is that one day our room was not made up, and we had to request extra towels.

The location is very close to a couple of Metro stops, and there were some great cafes and bakeries etc nearby, and attractions like the Pantheon are close. However the street the hotel is on is not particularly charming. The centre of Paris is only about a 15 minute walk though, so it's a pretty good option, and the price was reasonable.

What a lovely hotel!!! We were super impressed with it!! The room was modern and a decent size for 3 of us. The shower was the best we have ever used and my husband is still talking about it! The aircon was silent, the bedding, pillows and mattress were top class and the staff were really helpful and nothing was too much trouble for them! They have a facility where you can leave your luggage with them as we left really late the last day. The hotel is close to Metro's and buses and we would definitely stay here again if we went back to Paris.

Lovely boutique hotel very close to major sites. Got their early for a group tour and they held my luggage safely until the room was ready for check in. Hotel staff were very friendly, room is nicely sized and breakfast was delicious! Less than a block from the metro and within walking distance of some major sites!

For the price, this lovely little hotel cannot be beat. The rooms are tidy and comfortable and Paris sized. I was on the sixth floor with a lovely view of the quiet street below and Notre Dame to my left. The area around the hotel was just dreamy and perfect. There is the remains of a Roman amphitheater hidden across the street, lovely shops and cafes all around, walking distance to the best parts of Paris and a very short walk to the Metro station for explorations further afield. There is also a charming and disorganized second hand shop across the street that it irresistible to a person like me.

The best part was the staff. They were perfectly friendly and helpful and did everything to make me feel welcome and informed. My stay could not have been more perfect!

The position is strategic. Very close to metropolitan, many restaurants, facilities and the zone is pretty safe. The good match beetwen price-quality and the staff is very nice. My room was little but well organized.

Modern, clean, comfortable rooms in a great location in Paris. I quite enjoyed the area surrounding the hotel - lots of shops and restaurants that aren’t as packed with tourists as other neighborhoods. I particularly enjoyed the place de contrescape area located close to this hotel. We took a leisurely walk to the Louvre and Notre Dame from the hotel - close enough to walk on a beautiful day. Easy access to public transit. Only reason for four out of five stars is the WiFi - I stayed for two nights and was never able to send more than a text message over the WiFi. The signal, even in the lobby, wasn’t strong enough to make a call over the network or send a picture.

Myself and my family stayed here in two rooms, 1 twin, 1 double. This is a small hotel, very clean, great breakfast and lovely staff. It’s situated in a lovely, clean, pretty street not far from Notre Dame and the Seine. Everything is adequate and would not hedtitate to stay again, already considering returning next year. Loved it!

Beyond expectations, our balcony was a wonderful surprise. Staff so helpful with ice buckets, wine openers, restaurant suggestions and directions. Location was perfect for transit as well as just walking about and into the Notre Dame area (also viewable from out balcony) and along the water. Lots of shops and restaurants, cafes. without the mobs at the more tourist areas. When we go back to Paris we would definitely stay here again!

We stayed for 4 nights and had a lovely stay. The staff was extremely helpful and accommodating. The rooms are very clean, modern, comfortable and had all of the amenities we needed. We had no issues with noise from the street or other rooms. If you book on-line, breakfast is included in your stay. Breakfast options were the same every day, but had a nice variety. Restaurants, metro, and open air markets are just a short walk away. We would definitely recommend and would not hesitate to stay here again. Thank you for making our trip to Paris a wonderful experience!

The people who work here went out of the way to help us with everything from restaurant recommendations, dinner reservations, and scheduling a Pilates class. Although the room was quite small, we loved this very well-located quaint hotel. It was a pleasure to stay here. Special thanks to Leticia at the front desk!

Perfect hotel, we stayed for 3 nights in July, we were on the 6th floor (room 63) id requested a balcony via email before I arrived which they we able to accommodate me with - it had a view of the street and if you looked towards your left you could see the Norte Dame which was especially lovely when lit up in the evening. The room itself was clean, modern and tidy - it was small but all rooms in Paris are like this. The room had AC, hair dryer, safe, mini fridge everything you needed, bathroom was clean, the shower head was at a bit of a funny angle but this really wasn’t to much of an issue. The bed was extremely comfortable, no noise could be heard from the street however you could hear the next door room hair-drying and flushing the toilets but this was only very late at night when everything else was silent but again it wasn’t an issue. We didn’t have breakfast we chose to eat at local bakery’s in the mornings which were a lot cheaper. the location is perfect within walking distance to some major sights and only 2minute walk to the metro (which is VERY easy to use) we used this to get round much of Paris and to transfer from Gare Du Nord which is only around a 20min travel time. Hotel staff were lovely on the day we checked out we were able to leave our bags to do some last minute sightseeing and once arriving back they offered us coffees and water before we left. 5 Star Hotel *****

Within walking distance to everything--only a few minutes to Notre Dame and the river, and an easy taxi ride to Montmartre and Sacre Coeur. Close to the Louvre if you want to spend a day there, but if time is short, just walk through the Gardens and take the side streets for a more "local" view of Paris. Book directly on the hotel site for a better rate with breakfast included. Expect a small room (and a tiny lift) because this is Paris! If you're a bit claustrophobic, you can take the stairs up and down (as I did for this reason), so you might want to choose a lower floor.

The personnel at the front desk were accommodating, friendly and very helpful. The room was very small, expected in Paris. The bathroom wasn’t very clean, and the towels were a little stiff, not soft. The front desk referred us to an amazing French restaurant, La Maison de Verlaine - excellent prix fixed menu and I highly recommend!

This is a good hotel for a (mid)week in Paris. Rooms are not large, but all facilities available. Breakfast is good. Location is perfect when visiting Quartier Latin, its restaurants and sights nearby. Book directly with hotel to get best price.

Very disappointing. The room and bathroom were dirty, the mini fridge was not working, the room was tiny, barely room the move around. Poor value for money. The staff were kind and welcoming and the bed comfortable. The offer of a hot drink on arrival seemed like poor compensation for an all together disappointing experience.

Perfect location, very safe and lovely neighbourhood, close to the tube (less than 3 mins walk, Place Monge station has escalator to the ground so it’s convenient for travelers with heavy luggage), close to supermarket, many bakeries, restaurants. Just everything you need is close to the hotel.
The room is great, I stayed at the single room, really large room with good equipments, TV, water boiler, mini-refrigerator and in-room safe box makes my stay very convenient.
However, during my first day, the toilet had a smell of urine, other than this, overall the bathroom is very tidy and clean.
The staffs are nice and keen to provide help, the safe box had a little functioning promblem so the front desk staff immediately came to my room to reset it. They’re very friendly and helpful.
As a female solo traveler, this is the perfect hotel for me. Definitely recommend to everyone and will visit again!

The location is excellent. 50 m from Metro. Walking distance to Rue Mouftard, Quartier Latin, Pantheon and Seine. Room is tiny but bed is very comfortable. Bathroom is good. Don't expect a huge breakfast.

We stayed here for three nights and found the neighborhood to be safe. There were plenty of local shops, markets and cafes. Just walking around the neighborhood was a truly unique experience. We did see many of the tourist attractions but are glad we did not stay in the areas close to them. Many things were within walking distance and if we needed to use the Metro the station was close by. The rooms and bathrooms were small but we did expect that and it was clean and quite comfortable for us (2 adults). The staff was very helpful and friendly. We had our breakfast included and it was excellent. The coffee was perfect. Tables were nicely set when we walked in the dining area. The selection of food was very good and much better than the breakfasts we are used to at Hampton Inns. The bed was firm but very comfortable. We had a view of the street but when we shut the windows we didn't hear the traffic. I would stay here again. ( The only person I would not recommend this particular room for is anyone who is very large. Our shower was small but we are not big people. Perhaps they have larger showers in other rooms. ) Thank you Hotel des Nations for a wonderful stay in Paris!

Overall had a good experience. The room and specially the bathroom is not well maintained, it is not worth the money one pays for. However, the location is really good and is conveniently located near two metro stations. The breakfast is excellent and the staff are very welcoming.

Convenient friendly hotel in bustling neighborhood near two Metro stations. Building and rooms could use some updating but is comfortable with helpful staff. Good breakfast options with fruit, juices, meats, and croissants. Good spot for a few nights.

Perfect if you love the rive gauche of Paris. Room as expected from the website, clean and nice.
Very pleasent and friendly staff.
Very close to Rue Mouffetard where there is a beautiful market and also very close to Jardin du Luxembourg.

Excellent location in the Left Bank. Great for connecting to the metro with lots of shops and restaurants in the area. Don't miss sitting at the Place de l'Estrapade for an early evening drink before dinner. While the hotel and room will be considered very small by North American standards, set your expectations accordingly and you'll find the hotel charming. Very friendly and helpful staff.

My wife and I stayed here for 9 nights in late April-early May, 2018 and had an absolutely wonderful experience. First of all, the location is perfect...across the street from the Place Monge metro station and about 2 blocks from the Cardinal Lemoine station. Both stations provided us with easy access to all of the highlights of Paris. Secondly, we had a brief 10 minute walk to Rue Mouffetard which is a "must see" street in the Latin Quarter...full of cafes, restaurants, and bars. Third, the hotel staff were very helpful and congenial. Since we booked online with the hotel, our breakfast was included in the room rate and consisted of coffee, juices, pastries, fruit, cheeses, deli meats, cereals, eggs and sausage. Plenty to keep you going strong until mid-afternoon when it was time for coffee and baguette/pastry at one of the nearby boulangeries (bakeries). While the room size and amenities were perfectly fine, some larger framed folks might find fault with the small shower...but this was not an issue for us. In summary, the Hotel Des Nations was a wonderful place to stay in Paris and we would highly recommend to other travelers.

Well, Paris hotels are always a roulette, and for your 100something euro you have more chances to get a tiny, shabby and smelly room than something really nice. That’s why I’m so happy with Hotel des Nations, it’s really a win! Rooms are recently renovated with a good sense of style. ours was looking into inside yard and was very quite. Team was nice - we had a very early check-out and taxi was right in time. Also welcome coffee at the check-in is a nice touch. I loved the area near Sorbonne and 15 walk to Notre Dame. My advice is to book via hotel site - the price is much better then on booking and you can get a special offer with breakfast included. The only minus was WiFi - it was barely working in the evening, when everybody came back to the hotel. But, when you are in Paris, WiFi can wait -)

Great hotel with friendly staff. Very good location within walkdistance to notre dame, latin area and many others most see in Paris. Didnt have the breakfast, but it looked good. Family room was perfect

The rooms are small, but there was a little balcony from which we could see part of Notre Dame. The breakfast was basic--serve yourself buffet of yogurts, dried fruit, baguettes and croissants with jam and Nutella plus some hot items (limited in one metal heated serving pan) like bacon and pre-made scrambled eggs. I thought from the pictures that it would be nicer so was a bit disappointed, but if I had not had that expectation, I would have enjoyed it more because there is really nothing wrong with the hotel, and it's a great value. You need to walk about 15 minutes to get most places you would want to go, except for the Pantheon and the botanic gardens (Jardines des Plantes). It is a wonderful location for runners because you can run to the botanic gardens in 2 minutes (I timed it) and from there down and to the Seine with only one major road to cross (and once you get to the Seine, you can run as far as you want--stay at the river's edge so you avoid having to stop for traffic, which is an issue if you run up by the vendors, which is shadier but then you have to stop at lights). The hotel is close to two subway lines. To get here from Gard du Nord, you need to make a transfer though. Don't miss the Roman amphitheater ruins which are almost directly across from the hotel at 39 Rue Monge (it's a door that you pass through into what is left of the amphitheater and a little park). You can also get to them from a side street by going through the park directly, but it's fun to go through the door! Overall, I recommend this hotel if you are on a budget and want something clean and basic--I do think this hotel is the best you can get for around the 130-160 euro price point in Paris.
